{
  "stem": "11964.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the most painful memory was the moment we realized that we were separated from our parents.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was an experience which gave us not only pain but total, total, total [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] anguish.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were in pain because we didn't have them with us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we were in anguish because we didn't know what they are going to be subjected to.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the play of imagination was so brutal to us, to me, imagining as to how much pain they would have to endure and how painful it must have been for them to be separated from us and leave us behind.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the simple note from my mother who said, I'm sorry this is happening to us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She was such a noble person.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She was such an honest person.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My father and my mother were such human people, that I know that it must have torn their souls apart.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And this thought, this anguish, was to me the most painful emotion that I remember.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Another such emotion was when I was standing on the balcony of the people whose daughter I was tutoring, outside the ghetto in Warsaw, which was two blocks away from the Warsaw ghetto.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I was watching that ghetto going up in flames.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I had to sustain myself within me, to react similarly to the way they reacted, lest they would suspect me of not being as Polish as they were.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I remember the smell of the burning.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I remember the smoke and the flames.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "These were devastating times to me, much more devastating than some of the episodes.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
